Everything You Need To Know To Organize A Destination Wedding In Goa

 

I am sure every girl has thought about having a beach wedding once in her lifetime.Imagine exchanging your wedding vows on a beach side where the sun is setting in the background.Well what better beach destination to have the celebrations than Goa.Hosting a beach wedding it is a very doable these days.You can find tons of inspiration and ideas on Vow's n View's.

How much does it cost to have a destination wedding in Goa?

Usually a wedding in Goa would cost you anywhere around 30 -50 lakhs.This is only possible if you have about 100-150 guests who are invited for a maximum of 2 day wedding.The cost of any destination wedding in Goa would majorly depend on the following factors:

  • Venue: The venue of the celebration plays a major role in defining the budget for any destination wedding.For a Goa wedding you can choose from various beach resorts, shacks or budget hotels that have access to a private beach.Preferably a venue in south Goa is a better option as they are less crowded as compared to north Goa.Choose from a number of options available on Vow's n View's to get best prices and deals.
  • Number of days: Do not go overboard with the number of functions, it is better to restrict to a maximum of 3 day wedding.It is better to have 2 or more functions in a day so that you can have as many functions as you desire.
  • Guest list: Usually in case of destination wedding only close family members and a few friends are invited.In most cases the guests pay for their own travel tickets, however if you plan to book these for your guests, it is better that you book them much in advance.Bulk tickets booked in advance can help save a lot of money.
  • Other factors that affect the budget of your wedding are photographers, bridal makeup along with family makeup, decorators, catering and professional event planner. Various vendors are listed are on Vow's n View's, it helps you to look at different vendors from all across the country. Booking them is also is now just a few clicks away.

What are the top venues for a destination wedding in Goa?

The south part of the coastal state is a better choice for destination wedding as the beaches in south Goa are less crowded and much cleaner as compared to those in north Goa.It is easy to find good venues.

There are quite a few luxury hotels in Goa that beautiful properties to celebrate your marriage functions Alila Diwa Resortis a 5 star property that is surrounded by paddy fields the resort blends contemporary luxury with the magic of Goa's cultural richness. They have specially designed wedding packages that can also be customised according to you needs.

  • Price: On request
  • Capacity: 360-600 guests Taj group has a couple of properties in Goa such as the Taj Exotica Resort, Vivanta by Taj - Holiday Village and Vivanta by Taj, Panaji Grand Hyatt Resort is a luxurious property overlooking the bambolim bay. It has a grand banquet having a floating capacity of around 900 people and a lawn perfect for hosting outdoor events.
  • Price: Rs 5000 onwards
  • Capacity: 80- 860 guests Planet Hollywood Beach Resort symbolises Goan culture and is a hot destination wedding property in Goa. Overlooking the Utorda beach, the resort offers a beautiful setting for any ceremony.
  • Price: Rs 3000 onwards
  • Capacity: 210-350 guests

Apart from the luxury options, Goa also has many budget hotels options such as:

Hotel Goan Heritage is a budget hotel having a large lawn that is apt for hosting a large gathering as it can easily accommodate more than 1000 guests and an indoor banquet that is ideal to host a small gathering of about 200 people.

  • Price: Rs 650 onwards
  • Capacity: 150-1050 guests La Calypso Beach Resort is known for its hospitality and comfort of their guests is their top priority. The outdoor lawn has the capacity for about 1000 guests is a great budget venue option.
  • Price: Rs 1700
  • Capacity: 400-1000 guests Royal Orchid Beach Resort and Spa in Goa has both indoor banquet and a lush green outdoor lawn. This resort in Goa is surrounded by various beaches so getting the beachview is a surety.
  • Price: Rs 1200 onwards
  • Capacity: 120-1200 guests

Are you looking for wedding planners in Goa?

People generally think that hiring a wedding planner would increase their budget, but this is not always necessary. A professional always makes the planning much easy for anyone. In today’s time many hotels also provide these services for couples hosting destination wedding. The showcase on Vow's n View's has a number of wedding planners that will make the job easy for you so that you can enjoy the festivities. Some amazingly talented wedding planners based in Goa are:

Purple Tree Events Solution try to bridge the traditions with their contemporary ideas for different functions. They make sure that the personal style of both the bride and the groom is reflected in the events.

  • Starting price: Rs 4-6 lakh B3WeddingZ is one of the most popular wedding planning companies in Goa. Their team is quite efficient and well trained makes sure that they fulfill each and every wish of the couple.
  • Starting price: Rs 2.5-4 lakh

What is the best time to plan a wedding in Goa?

The weather condition of Goa are quite pleasant throughout the year, however winter wedding is a better idea as during the summer season it can get a little humid in Goa and rains can be unpredictable.

Tying the knot in the off season is a better idea as there will be less tourists in the city. Also there are high chances that you will get discounts and can get venues and accommodations at a cheaper rate.

How to reach Goa?

  • By Air: Dabolim airport is the sole airport in Goa.There are numerous flights that reach Goa on a daily basis
  • By Train: There are 2 railway stations in Goa - Madgaon and Vasco- da - gama.Goa is well connected to other parts of maharashtra as well as the whole country.
  • By Road: Kadamba is the main bus stand in panaji and different bus services are available.The highways are smooth and well maintained, so driving to Goa from nearby cities like mumbai and karnataka is also very convenient.

For travelling within the city cabs are easily available.

How to accommodate your guests?

Accommodating your guests at the same place as the venue of your event can surely help you save quite a lot of money.Usually hotels give huge discounts on bulk bookings for rooms.

This also helps in cutting down the transportation cost as well as the travelling time.

However in case accommodation at the venue is not possible then make sure that you look for hotels that are very close to it.

How to host a budget wedding in Goa?

Hosting a wedding in Goa well within your budget is not very difficult.Keeping in mind the following points can definitely help you to save some money:

  • Destination wedding means only close family and friends are to be invited.
  • Choose your venues wisely.
  • Book accommodation at the same place as events.
  • Make all your bookings as early as possible.
  • Wrap up the functions in maximum 3 days.
  • Don't go over the top in terms of decor.
  • Book as many local vendors as possible.
  • Choose off season for your wedding date.

What Is The Best Time To Have A Wedding In Goa?

It’s always a good time to organize a wedding in Goa, however, we would still recommend going for a winter wedding.Temperatures in Goa during the summers(March- May) can get unpredictable, with heat spells and rains.If you are among the very few who wish to organise an indoor Goan wedding, the humidity in the air can make everything stressful for you and your guests alike.So, we recommend organizing your wedding during the Winter season.While the air can get a little chilly during January, it’s never too cold here!

Pleasant temperature, with breezy air means you can organize functions during the day as well, thereby reducing costs by 30 %.After all, you can then cut down on extra lighting and power backup.Also, pictures come out better in natural light!

How To Save Costs When Organizing A Destination Wedding In Goa ?

Beach Weddings are possibly the biggest trend of recent years, and we don’t see it dying anytime soon.After all, what could be better than combining your wedding celebrations and a beach vacation together ? But that doesn’t necessarily mean you will have to shell out more money.Here is how you can have a Beach Wedding on a budget -

  • Choose your location wisely - A place that looks naturally pretty would mean saving unnecessary expenses on decor.
  • Choose an off - season wedding date - This is a no - brainer.Prices of all services go down during off - seasons.You will also have better chances to get exciting discounts!
  • Book accommodation and events at the same venue - More possibility of getting discounts due to bulk booking, and reduced transportation costs! Also, this will help you save time during the celebrations.
  • Book as soon as possible - The sooner you book, the better chances you have to get cheaper deals.Also, if you make bulk bookings, you’ll be in a better position.
  • Keep your itenary crisp - Do not organise a lot of events - restrict to a 1 to max 3 day wedding.And keep your guest list as crisp as possible.We would recommend about 50 - 100 people.
  • Save on food and beverages by choosing local dishes and drinks for the wedding.Also exercise restraint in the number of items on the menu.

How To Integrate Goan Culture In Your Wedding ?

Goa is one of the most happening and modern wedding destinations in India.Ofcourse, nothing can beat the chill vibes at a beach wedding, but that’s not all that Goa has to offer.You can make Goan culture a part of your celebrations to add a twist to your celebrations.Include the mouth watering seafood, and local dishes in your menu - Portuguese, Konkan and Bahamani cuisines to treat your guests to an exotic delight!

If your dreams of a fairytale wedding have always included a majestic palace background with hints of royalty and old world charm, then what could be better than a destination wedding in Jaipur? December to February can get really chilly and cold at Jim Corbett. Add the desired products to your shopping bag, proceed to checkout, select delivery address and proceed to payment. On payment page, select EMI (Credit Card) under payment options and follow these simple steps:

Shipping Policy

 

How Can I Track My Order?

To check the status of your order, please visit the ‘Order History’ section in ‘My Dashboard’ and find your order. Once your order has been shipped, you can track your order by entering the tracking number provided by us on our shipping partners’ websites.

 

How Are Orders Placed On Keen By Shirin Delivered To Me?

All orders placed on Keen by Shirin are dispatched through our trusted courier partners such as DTDC, Delhivery and Blue Dart

 

Will All The Products Be Shipped Together?

To ensure the best experience, we ideally ship all products of an order together. However, there might be instances where some products are ready to get shipped earlier than other products. To make sure that you don't wait even a minute longer than you have to, sometimes we ship an order in parts if some products are not ready. You can track the shipment of your pending products in the ‘Order History’ section under ‘My Dashboard’. We make sure that you are notified via Mail and SMS when each item of your order is shipped.

 

What are the shipping charges?

We offer Free Shipping on all orders delivered within India.

For International Orders, shipping charges are as follows:

  • Order up to Rs. 20,000: Shipping charges are calculated as per actual weight and delivery location.
  • Order from Rs.20,000- Rs.40,000 : Flat Rs.5000
  • Orders above Rs. 40,000: Rs.8000

Customs Duties & taxes, if any, are to be borne by the customer.

 

What does Ready To Ship mean?

‘Ready to Ship’ means that we can dispatch a product within 2 days, and deliver it within 4-5 days. You can explore our ‘Ready to Ship’ collection by going to the ‘Shop’ section of our website. These delivery timelines are only possible for orders within India.

 

What does estimated delivery time mean?

Estimated delivery time is the time we anticipate it will take for your order to reach you. Since a lot of products are made-to-order, the estimated delivery time can range between 2-4 weeks. The exact delivery time is written in the ‘Shipping’ section of each order. International orders can take up to a week longer than the shipping time mentioned, and ‘Ready to Ship’ orders will arrive (both domestically and internationally) much sooner.

 

Can you expedite the delivery of a product?

Sorry, currently we do not have any service available to expedite delivery of any products. In the future, if we are offering such services and your pin code is serviceable, you will receive communication from our end.

 

How do I pay for my order?

Customers within India can pay online through Net Banking, Debit/Credit Cards, Google Pay, UPI or PayPal. Cash on delivery is also available for shipments within India for orders up to Rs. 20,000. For international orders, we accept payment via International Debit/Credit Cards (Visa, Master Card, AMEX), and PayPal.

 

Why is COD not offered in my location?

International location are not covered for COD by our delivery partners. Any inconvenience you face is regretted. And if this is the case, you will only see options for online payments such as Credit Card, Debit Card, Net Banking, Paypal or UPI.

 

My Order Status shows Out For Delivery but I haven’t received it yet – when will it be delivered?

On the day your order is out for delivery, you will receive an SMS on your registered mobile number and you will receive another SMS after the order is delivered. Our courier partners will contact you in case you were not available at the delivery location during the first delivery attempt.

 

I missed the delivery of my order, what should I do?

If you were unavailable during our courier partner’s first attempt to deliver your order, the courier will contact you on your registered mobile number to make sure you’re home before re-attempting delivery. They will attempt to deliver your package 3 times before returning it to our fulfillment center. If you miss all 3 delivery attempts and the product is in our fulfillment center, you can request that we re-dispatch the product (as long as it is available).

 

Can I open a shipment before accepting it?

Our courier partner will hand over the package to you to open only once the payment has been made. If there is an issue with your order, you can contact us on +91-9313846800 or info@vowsnviews.com, or raise a Return/Exchange request from the ‘My Dashboard’ section.

 

My order is delayed. When can I expect it?

To check the expected delivery date of your order, please visit the ‘Order History’ section in ‘My Dashboard' or email us on info@vowsnviews.com. You can also call our Customer Care Helpline on +91-9313846800 from Monday - Friday between 11 am - 7 pm and on Saturdays between 12 am - 6.00 pm.

 

The product I ordered has gone out of stock, why wasn’t I informed earlier?

On some occasions, some of our partner brands are unable to fulfill orders for certain products listed on our platform due to supply issues. On other occasions, we do not dispatch an order if we are unhappy with the product quality. If either of these scenarios occurs, you will be notified immediately and a full refund (in case the order was pre-paid) will be processed.

 

I placed an order through Cash on Delivery facility, but now I want to pay using Debit/Credit/Netbanking. How can I do this?

Currently, we don’t have a provision to convert COD orders to prepaid orders at the time of delivery, but we can convert your order to pre-paid if it has not been shipped yet. You can request for the same by emailing us on info@vowsnviews.com.

 

Do you deliver internationally?

Yes, we deliver products across all continents (except Antarctica :P). International delivery timelines range between 2-5 weeks. To know the exact delivery date, please refer to the ‘Shipping’ section on the product page or contact our customer care.

 

What are the international shipping charges?

fields.title: Is it Really so Difficult to plan a Wedding During Pandemic? I Got You Covered!
fields.description:
"As always, take care of yourself. Honestly, its OK to cry. Its OK to be angry or to feel a wide range of emotions," says Alison Laesser


 
It's obvious that weddings in the near future are postponed or not happened like it was suppose to. But, do you believe in the saying "Whatever happens, happens for good" ? or does the question pops on your mind that why do we need to gather so many people who we don't even know if they are happy with our marriage or not? Why not have a simple subtle wedding with your closest ones who actually are happy to see you happy? When you look at a brighter side to it you realise that COVID-19 pandemic helps you to trigger these thoughts.
 
 
How hard is to plan a small wedding?

Well, the main concerns are health risks, guest safety, and, government COVID-19 guidelines, PERIOD! But, have you ever gave it a thought that how fun it could be to plan an intimate wedding with your loved ones? How amazingly you can cherish each moment with each one of them?

 These questions pop on my mind ever since the pandemic hit our country. 
I get it when my clients say that what are we going to do? we can't cancel it or postpone it. Nobody is asking you to postpone it. I mean, certainly not my team. There are many articles on how can you plan a wedding or 5 things you should do while planning your wedding, which are a good read, trust me.




It is hard to plan a wedding when you have a vast number of guest lists to take care of. Now look! How many guests you have? 50? 100? God!! I wish to have an opportunity to invite only 50-100 people at my wedding. Believe it or not.
 
You guys want your wedding to be a dream to be cherished forever? Obviously you want that, who doesn't?

About Kajal Kaushal Professional Makeup Artist -

Kajal Kaushal is a renowned  Makeup Artist based out of Delhi, NCR. She holds exquisite skills to give a stunning makeover to anyone and everyone. She offers all makeup and hairstyling services. Bridal makeup is her field of expertise. The cosmetic & beauty products used by her are of high quality and well acclaimed. She is a master in creating picture-worthy looks with her makeup skills. From bridal makeup to special occasion makeup, she offers all types of makeup services. Other than makeup and hairstyling she also provides the facility of draping, hair-nail extensions, hair accessories, false lashes, coloured non-powdered lenses and many more.

Kajal provides the makeup services by her in Delhi NCR region and outstation as well , the charges for the same may vary accordingly.
